  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nAnvil\r\n\r\n### Describe the feature you would like\r\n\r\nethers-rs (transaction) types are used to construct request types.\r\nAnvil has to deal with the same data, but has a different purpose and the ethers types are not always practical, plus some support for deserialization was missing at the time.\r\n\r\ntherefore I created some duplicate types and implemented a compatibility layer between Anvil's tx types and the ethers types, which seemed more practical at the time.\r\n\r\nHowever, I think we can try to unify them and get rid of some code this way, ref https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/pull/2010\r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n\r\nI'd like to get rid of anvil's TypedTransactionRequest entirely and replace it with ethers TypedTransaction\r\nso we don't need this https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/master/anvil/core/src/eth/transaction/ethers_compat.rs\r\nsame for anvil's Log type \r\nnot sure about TypedReceipt yet\r\nreason why I added another log type was for easy From/Into revm::Log\r\nand the reason for another TypedTransactionRequest was basically to have a nicer representation for kind which represents the to field\r\nethers has NamedOrAddress which makes it a bit tedious to handle in anvil\r\n\r\n_No response_",
